Dear @sarahd_gb , 

I wish you all the best, especially with the difficulty of the corona situation, and I hope your training is going very well. I saw your video, and while I agree completely that corruption in the IWF must be addressed, and change must happen, I have few questions as an athlete that you represent in the IWF meetings .

1) You said that delegates from countries that have been disqualified from the Olympic Games and world championships cannot serve as representatives on the executive board. Why is it that clean athletes from these nations cannot argue for their interests? Do you consider athletes to be clean after they have served their penalties for previous violations? For example, can we count Loredana , sohrab moradi and @tani240191 clean athletes? If your answer is yes about those athletes- how can we give them the chance to compete in the Olympic Games without giving permission to @mohamed_ehab_youssef from Egypt, who has never been disqualified, but his country has been is disqualified from the Olympic Games? There is no consistency and we all suffer from athletes who do not compete clean. There are some athletes that broke the rules, have been disqualified in the past and received their first warning, and today have permission to compete without a red mark. 
- 2) Do you have a personal interest in using this situation to get an Olympic spot by removing the Olympic personal qualification for the two Romanian athletes (@tomaloredanaelena and Irina Lepsa) in your category? Should the clean athletes in red mark countries also be blocked from competing in the Olympic Games?

- 3) - Athletes like @kianoush_rostami , @sohrab.moradiii , and many other athletes that have been set back by cancelled competitions due to COVID-19, or were injured: >>continue in comments

אני מאוד רוצה לשתף אתכם - אני מאוד אוהבת את המדינה שלי - מדינת ישראל ❤️ אני הכי גאה לייצג את המדינה שלנו, אני הכי גאה להיות יהודיה , זה כבוד הכי גדול בקיומנו. למה אני רוצה לשתף אתכם ? כי יש לנו היסטוריה ארוכה כל כך, והיסטוריה הכי מעניינת מכל שאר המדינות . מדינה כל כך קטנה אבל כל כך בולטת . 
אני גאה להיות בתחום הרמת המשקולות מכל מיני סיבות ואחת מהן היא בשנת 1972 באולימפיאדת מינכן בה נהרגו ספורטאים יהודים ורובם היו מתחום הרמת המשקולות, מאז ענף המשקולות פשוט קרס עד היום. אני גאה להיות חלק מענף ספורט כל כך קשה, כל כך לא מפותח שצנח מאז אותה טרגדיה. 
אני אמשיך לקדם את הענף עד לתחייתו המלאה 
ולהביא הישגים וגאווה.
@allinisrael @rocktape_il @turbine_israel @maccabi_telaviv_sport @olympicteamisrael @weightlifting_israel ....................
................. I would love to share with you why I love my country 🇮🇱 I am honored and proud to represent israel, and proud to be Jewish. The Jewish people have a beautiful and rich history. 
I am proud to be a weightlifter for many reasons. But one reason is in the wake of the unspeakable tragedy at the 1972 Munich Olympics (Munich massacre.) This was an attack by a Palestinian terrorist group that took the lives of eleven members of the Israeli Olympic team. Four of them were part of the weightlifting team. Since then, weightlifting in israel has fallen apart- until today. I am proud to do this sport because it has been difficult to develop in our country since the tragedy. I will continue to promote the industry, and try to bring more Achievements and pride to our country. 🙏🇮🇱❤
